  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Hawaii total $2.1B in FY2026 to date, with 18,704 awards and an average award size of $112K. Obligations are down 62.0% year over year. The Department of Defense accounts for the bulk of current-year spending, with $1.6B in obligations, followed by the General Services Administration at $248M and the Department of Homeland Security at $102M. Construction and engineering sectors dominate award dollars: Other Heavy and Civil Engineering Construction is $602M and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction is $362M. Major vendors include DRAGADOS/HAWAIIAN DREDGING/ORION JV at $354M and NAN INC at $272M. Fiscal-year history shows a peak at $6.7B in FY24 and a decline to $5.5B in FY25 before the current FY26 to date total of $2.1B. The note that current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date) applies to all FY2026 to date figures. This overview focuses on current obligations, agency concentration, industry distribution, and the leading vendors by dollar value.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How have obligations trended across recent fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations rose from $2.8B in FY21 to $6.7B in FY24 and then fell to $5.5B in FY25. FY26 to date obligations stand at $2.1B. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Year-over-year change for FY2026 to date is down 62.0%."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which industries and vendors account for the most spending in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "Other Heavy and Civil Engineering Construction leads industries with $602M, followed by Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $362M and Engineering Services at $244M. The top vendor is DRAGADOS/HAWAIIAN DREDGING/ORION JV with $354M, followed by NAN INC at $272M and CONTI FEDERAL SERVICES, LLC at $97.3M. Construction and engineering-related industries and vendors dominate the FY2026 to date totals."
      }
    ]
  },
